Corporations like Fiat-Chrysler who make Jeeps are always looking for ways to sell their product. Stealing the good memories from a beloved movie and inserting a product to sell removes any meaning from movies (or songs) and replaces it with a commercial one.
"Thanks" to attention starved Bill Murray and Jeep and the ad agency who created this campaign for commercially defiling the memory of a sweet funny wise movie like "Groundhog Day" which will now forever be associated with an unreliable vehicle.
